comments: Each shape had a name, as did each colour. I found it easier to remember colours, so I memorised those first, followed by the shapes. Some shapes/colours sounded like English words that I could relate to. For example, red = ishu; if you see red, that's an issue (that's how I remembered it). One of the shapes sounded like gaffe. Also, wop seems like a round word (somehow) and zet sounds like a spiky word (somehow).
